(firstQuint)Study of Escitalopram in the Treatment of Specific Phobia.

 This double-blind placebo-controlled pilot trial study is designed to assess the efficacy of 12 weeks of escitalopram vs.

 placebo in the treatment of specific phobia in adult outpatients.

 It is hypothesized that escitalopram is safe and effective in the treatment of specific phobia.

